HEADWORD: Hende
<hw>Hende</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE., near, handy, kind,
fr. AS. <ets>gehende</ets> near, fr. <ets>hand</ets> hand. See
<er>Handy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Skillful; dexterous;
clever.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Friendly; civil; gentle; kind.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hendecagon</ent>⟦br⟧
